A new report urges a radical shift that would include allowing the remaining abalone population to be harvested to the point where there’s so little left that the illegal market crashes. The Zondo Commission has found that the value of crooked contracts given to Bosasa by government departments was at least R2.37bn. And the ANC is deeply implicated in the skulduggery. Report finds Dudu Myeni received a Louis Vuitton bag stuffed with R300,000 bribe and helped halt the Bosasa corruption probe. Former president Jacob Zuma’s confidante, docket-squasher-in-chief, and his charity's chairperson, is in a lot of trouble.